config BR2_PACKAGE_LZMA_SDK
	bool "lzma-sdk"
	help
	  7-Zip's LZMA SDK (Igor Pavlov's reference LZMA
	  implementation), compiled as a shared library (liblzma-sdk)
	  for Main_MiSTer -- which vendors this exact C code as
	  lib/lzma/ -- and for libchdr, whose CHD v5 LZMA codec is
	  written against this SDK's API. Pure single-threaded C
	  (built under Z7_ST), so it needs no toolchain thread or C++
	  dependencies.

	  This is NOT xz-utils' liblzma.so.5: entirely different API
	  (LzmaDec_*/LzmaEnc_*/LzmaCompress vs lzma_stream_*), and xz
	  is packaged separately by upstream Buildroot as 'xz'.

	  Named "lzma-sdk" rather than plain "lzma" because upstream
	  Buildroot already ships a host-only package/lzma (lzma-utils
	  4.32.7) squatting the unprefixed LZMA_ Make namespace; a
	  same-named package here would silently corrupt host-lzma's
	  download variables rather than error out (the full mechanism
	  is documented in lzma-sdk.mk's header comment).

	  https://www.7-zip.org/sdk.html
